<br>
I am new to the Wizard class.<br>
<br>
But not to the port class(53 Druid).<br>
<br>
So here's my take on it.<br>
<br>
You are providing a service, time to do the port and time that it took you to get to that level.  And thus saving them time in running.<br>
<br>
Time is money.  Frankly, you earned it.<br>
<br>
Why not accept the donation?  In some cultures it is an enormous offense to refuse a gift.<br>
<br>
I have hacked this topic this way and that way for about a year and a half on the Druid boards.  Norrath takes all kinds,,,from shouting port whores, to those that accept donations, to those that only do it for free, to those that do not port strangers.<br>
<br>
&quot;Good luck finding a group&quot;<br>
And one other question to you, where were all his Druid and Wizard friends that evening, why did not his group port him around?  I would hazard a guess he has few of those.<br>
<br>
Frankly, the warrior was an idiot(or maybe his younger brother got on his char).  Or as others have said &quot;prick&quot;.  Right HIS name down, and when he wants to go on those high level raids with you later, then YOU can decline him.   Don't write him off, write him down.  Use the command /note Dumbass the Warrior gets not more ports from me.<br>
<br>
And just tell me when you are killing in LoIO or SK who usually does all the looting when you are grouped.  When I was that age, it weren't the casters, I will tell you. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=berdug0>berdug0</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(8/17/01 10:22:23 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: hehe</span><hr size=1> Cheapie bastard.<br>
